Forensic investigators are carefully combing the scene where at least 22 youngsters aged between 18 and 20 years old were found dead at the Enyobeni Tavern. The incident occurred in the early hours of Sunday morning at the tavern in Scenery Park, East London. Updates will appear below. Please refresh the tab if required.  While the cause of the deaths is unknown at this stage, Eastern Cape police spokesperson Brigadier Tembinkosi Kinana said investigations are underway.  Meanwhile, Police Minister Bheki Cele had to excuse himself from a live interview as he broke down in tears.  Cele later said: “It’s a terrible scene. They are pretty young. When you are told they are 13 years, 14 years and you go there and you see them. It breaks (you).” On Sunday evening, the South African Police Service (Saps) ordered the deployment of maximum resources as police investigate the circumstances surrounding the incident.  As per the police, the death of 21 teenagers will be investigated after their “lifeless bodies [were found at] a local tavern.  “Upon arrival police found seventeen bodies inside the building. It was later established two more died at a local clinic, one died en route to hospital and another died in hospital.”  “Nine of the deceased are female while twelve of the deceased are male.” NOW READ: Enyobeni Tavern: Saps investigating liquor legislation compliance